main event: A civilian couple in Panama City, Florida observed a star-like object in the sky that moved slowly and silently from west to east before quickly disappearing.
interesting points: The object did not move like a falling star and did not leave a trail or tail.
The object moved at a high rate of speed and was out of sight in less than a minute.
The witnesses were unsure of what the object was and did not wish to report it to the Air Force's 'Little Blue Book' program.
The report was made to the Project Blue Book program, which was the U.S. Air Force's official investigation of UFO sightings.
The report indicates that the witnesses believed the object was some kind of 'trouble' or something that 'did not belong to them'.
